# report-export

## Functionality
Generates professional compliance reports in PDF and DOCX formats. Uses a hybrid approach: TypeScript service for data preparation + R script for document rendering via R Markdown templates. Also supports client-side PDF generation via jsPDF as a fallback.

## Tasks
- Format assessment results into structured report data
- Generate PDF reports via R Markdown (`generate_report.R`)
- Generate DOCX reports via R Markdown (`generate_report.R`)
- Include compliance tables, summary statistics, and status indicators
- Client-side PDF generation via `jspdf` + `jspdf-autotable` as fallback
- Provide download triggers from the UI header "Export" buttons

## Purpose
Environmental compliance reports are **legal and regulatory documents**. This module produces professional, printable reports that environmental engineers can submit to regulators, attach to permit applications, or archive for compliance records.

## General Roadmap
- Currently `services/report-export.ts` (~13KB) for TS logic + `generate_report.R` for R-based rendering
- Supports two generation paths: R Markdown (requires R) and pure JS (jsPDF fallback)
- Future: custom report templates
- Future: branded reports with company logo/headers

## Key Files
- `services/report-export.ts` — Report data prep and jsPDF fallback
- `src-tauri/scripts/generate_report.R` — R Markdown report generation (PDF/DOCX)
- `services/analytics.ts` — `ReportInput`, `ReportResult` types + `generateReport()` function
